## Container Breakdown (4 services)

### 1. `bolna-app` — The Core Engine (port 5001)

| Aspect | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| **Dockerfile** | [dockerfiles/bolna_server.Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/dockerfiles/bolna_server.Dockerfile) |
| **Base** | `python:3.10.13-slim` |
| **Key deps** | `ffmpeg`, `gcc`, `g++`, `libgomp1`, `git` |
| **Python pkg** | Installs `bolna` from GitHub master via pip |
| **Entry** | `uvicorn quickstart_server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 5001` |
| **Volumes** | `../agent_data` → `/app/agent_data`, AWS creds (read-only) |

**What it runs ([quickstart_server.py](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/quickstart_server.py)):**

A FastAPI app providing:

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/agent` | `POST` | Create agent → stores config in Redis, prompts to local file |
| `/agent/{id}` | `GET` | Fetch agent config from Redis |
| `/agent/{id}` | `PUT` | Update agent config |
| `/agent/{id}` | `DELETE` | Delete agent from Redis |
| `/all` | `GET` | List all agents |
| `/chat/v1/{agent_id}` | `WebSocket` | **The real-time voice pipeline** — accepts WebSocket, loads agent config from Redis, creates [AssistantManager](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/bolna/agent_manager/assistant_manager.py#14-66), runs tasks |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The WebSocket endpoint at `/chat/v1/{agent_id}` is the heart of the system. This is where the telephony providers (Twilio/Plivo) stream audio to, and where [AssistantManager](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/bolna/agent_manager/assistant_manager.py#14-66) orchestrates the ASR→LLM→TTS pipeline in real-time.

### 2. `redis` — Persistence Layer (port 6379)

- Stores agent configurations as JSON strings keyed by `agent_uuid`
- No persistence volume = **data is lost on container restart**
- Prompt files stored separately on filesystem at `agent_data/{uuid}/conversation_details.json`

### 3. [ngrok](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/telephony_server/twilio_api_server.py#24-40) — Public URL Tunneling (port 4040)

Creates 3 tunnels so external services (Twilio/Plivo) can reach local containers:

| Tunnel Name | Target | Purpose |
|-------------|--------|---------|
| `twilio-app` | `twilio-app:8001` | Twilio webhook callbacks |
| `plivo-app` | `plivo-app:8002` | Plivo webhook callbacks |
| `bolna-app` | `bolna-app:5001` | WebSocket streaming endpoint |

> [!WARNING]
> The ngrok auth token in [ngrok-config.yml](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/ngrok-config.yml) appears to have a placeholder token `<3AIRr...>`. This needs a real token from [ngrok.com](https://ngrok.com).

### 4. `twilio-app` / `plivo-app` — Telephony Bridges (ports 8001/8002)

These are lightweight FastAPI servers that bridge telephony providers to bolna:

**Call flow (Twilio example):**
1. `POST /call` receives `{agent_id, recipient_phone_number}`
2. Fetches ngrok tunnel URLs from `http://ngrok:4040/api/tunnels`
3. Calls `twilio_client.calls.create()` with callback URL pointing to `/twilio_connect`
4. Twilio calls the number, then calls back to `/twilio_connect`
5. `/twilio_connect` returns TwiML that opens a `<Stream>` to `wss://bolna-app/chat/v1/{agent_id}`
6. Audio now flows bidirectionally: Phone ↔ Twilio ↔ WebSocket ↔ Bolna

**Plivo has the same pattern** but uses Plivo's XML format with `<Stream bidirectional="true">` and adds a `/plivo_hangup_callback` endpoint.

---

## Call Flow Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as You (API call)
    participant Telephony as Twilio/Plivo App
    participant Ngrok as ngrok
    participant TelCloud as Twilio/Plivo Cloud
    participant Phone as 📞 Recipient
    participant Bolna as bolna-app
    participant Redis as Redis
    participant ASR as Deepgram
    participant LLM as OpenAI
    participant TTS as ElevenLabs

    User->>Telephony: POST /call {agent_id, phone}
    Telephony->>Ngrok: GET /api/tunnels
    Ngrok-->>Telephony: public URLs
    Telephony->>TelCloud: Create call w/ callback URL
    TelCloud->>Phone: Ring 📞
    Phone-->>TelCloud: Answer
    TelCloud->>Telephony: Callback → /twilio_connect
    Telephony-->>TelCloud: TwiML → Stream to bolna WS
    TelCloud->>Bolna: WebSocket connect /chat/v1/{agent_id}
    Bolna->>Redis: Get agent config
    Redis-->>Bolna: Agent JSON
    
    loop Real-time conversation
        Phone->>TelCloud: Audio
        TelCloud->>Bolna: WS audio frames
        Bolna->>ASR: Transcribe audio
        ASR-->>Bolna: Text
        Bolna->>LLM: Generate response
        LLM-->>Bolna: Streamed text
        Bolna->>TTS: Synthesize speech
        TTS-->>Bolna: Audio chunks
        Bolna->>TelCloud: WS audio response
        TelCloud->>Phone: Play audio 🔊
    end
```

---

## The Quickstart Client ([quickstart_client.py](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/quickstart_client.py))

An alternative to telephony — a **local audio client** that connects directly to bolna's WebSocket:

- Uses **PyAudio** for microphone input (16kHz, mono, PCM16)
- Uses **sounddevice** for speaker output (24kHz, mono, PCM16)
- Sends base64-encoded audio frames over WebSocket
- Handles `"clear"` messages for **interruption support** (stops playing, clears buffer)

> [!NOTE]
> This client connects to `ws://localhost:5001` directly, bypassing telephony entirely. Useful for testing without phone numbers.

