## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose | Required For |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `DEEPGRAM_AUTH_TOKEN` | ASR (speech-to-text) | Core |
| `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` | TTS (text-to-speech) | Core |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | LLM responses | Core |
| `OPENAI_MODEL` | Default model (`gpt-3.5-turbo`) | Core |
| `REDIS_URL` | Redis connection (`redis://redis:6379`) | Core |
| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio auth | Twilio only |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio auth | Twilio only |
| `TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER` | Caller ID | Twilio only |
| `PLIVO_AUTH_ID` | Plivo auth | Plivo only |
| `PLIVO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Plivo auth | Plivo only |
| `PLIVO_PHONE_NUMBER` | Caller ID | Plivo only |
| `AMBIENT_NOISE_PRESETS_DIR` | Path to noise presets | Optional |

---

## Key Observations & Points for Brainstorming

### ✅ Strengths
1. **Clean separation of concerns** — Telephony, AI orchestration, and storage are properly isolated into separate containers
2. **Provider-agnostic** — Supports multiple ASR/LLM/TTS/telephony providers via plug-in architecture
3. **Real-time streaming** — WebSocket-based bidirectional audio with interruption support
4. **Docker-first** — Easy to spin up locally with `docker compose up`
5. **Agent CRUD API** — Full REST API for creating/managing agents with JSON configs

### ⚠️ Concerns / Improvement Areas

1. **No Redis persistence** — The Redis container has no volume mount; all agent data is lost on restart
2. **Bolna installed from GitHub master** — The Dockerfile `pip install`s from `git+https://github.com/bolna-ai/bolna@master`. This means:
   - No version pinning → builds can break unpredictably
   - Not using the local source code at all
3. **ngrok token exposed** — The auth token is in [ngrok-config.yml](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/ngrok-config.yml) (should be in [.env](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/.env))
4. **No health checks** — Docker Compose has no health check definitions; services depend on each other but can't verify readiness
5. **`redis.keys("*")`** — The `/all` endpoint scans all Redis keys, which is a known anti-pattern for production
6. **No authentication** — All endpoints are open with CORS `allow_origins=["*"]`
7. **AWS creds mounted** — The docker-compose mounts `~/.aws/credentials` into the container (for AWS Polly TTS)
8. **Windows compatibility** — [start.sh](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/start.sh) is a bash script; won't run natively on Windows without WSL

### 🔍 Questions to Explore

1. **What's our telephony provider?** Twilio or Plivo? Or do we want to use the local client ([quickstart_client.py](file:///c:/Users/Farook/Genfox-Works/Realaty/bolna/local_setup/quickstart_client.py)) without telephony?
2. **Do we need to modify the bolna core**, or just the local_setup wrapper?
3. **What's the target deployment?** Local Docker only, or cloud (AWS/GCP/Azure)?
4. **What AI provider stack** are we targeting? (Which ASR, LLM, TTS?)
5. **Do we need the ambient noise feature?** (3 WAV presets: call-center, coffee-shop, office-ambience)
6. **Should we add persistence** to Redis (volume mount) or use a different store?

